This is the README file for IPC::Cmd -- a cross platform way of running
(interactive) commandline programs.

Please type "perldoc IPC::Cmd" after installation to see the module
usage information.

#####################################################################

* Description

IPC::Cmd
    Allows for the searching and execution of any binary on your system.
    It adheres to verbosity settings and is able to run intereactive. It
    also has an option to capture output/error buffers.

#####################################################################

* Installation

IPC::Cmd uses the standard perl module install process:

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install

